An Argia plana is a species of damselfly found primarily in North America. 
It features a slender body with a length of approximately 20-30mm and a wingspan of 35-45mm. 
The slender body is usually black with blue markings on the thorax and abdomen. 
The wings of the Argia plana are transparent and iridescent, with a slight blue or purple hue. 
This species can commonly be found near streams, rivers, and other aquatic habitats such as ponds and marshes. 
They are active during the day and often fly quickly, making short flights to catch insect prey. 
The Argia plana is a common damselfly species in its range and is considered a valuable indicator of the health of aquatic ecosystems in its habitat.
